RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 83. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE AUGUST 1 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHERILINDA was hustled away from the gate and assumed command in the early running, set the pace into the backstretch run, showed the way while mildly pressured through the backstretch run, carved out a decent pace while well handled into the second turn, raced in hand into upper stretch and drew to a clear lead at the furlong marker, was given a few taps of the crop into deep stretch and was hand ridden to the finish to be much the best. KERRYGOLD LADY broke alertly then settled off of the decent early pace, saved ground into the backstretch run then was steered outside of rivals heading to the half-mile marker, came three wide into the stretch, rallied in the final furlong, could not impact the winner at the finish and bested the rest. AGREETODISAGREE stalked the early pace while outside of rivals, maintained a three wide path to the half-mile marker, chased SHERILINDA to the quarter pole, could not keep pace with SHERILINDA into the lane, weakened in deep stretch and held clearly in the end for third. DANGEROUS ILLUSION had her head turned at the start and was unprepared leaving the break, was allowed to settle through the backstretch run, went two then three wide along the far turn and did not offer a late response. SPLICER lacked early speed, saved ground into the far turn, raced two wide into the stretch and did not factor. PRANCIN N THE PARK was forwardly placed into the first turn and stalked from a two wide path into the backstretch run, attended to the decent fractions to the half-mile marker, lost position into the far turn and gave way in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 5F All Weather Track CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAJOR TOM raced close to the decent early pace, saved ground along the turn and tracked the pacesetter to the quarter marker, raced a bit in tight into upper stretch, found room and mounted an inside bid nearing the furlong marker, dueled with his stablemate into deep stretch, took a narrow lead in the final yards, drifted out under firm left-handed urging just before the wire and held on for the win at the finish. O'BANION (IRE) raced close to the decent early pace, tracked two wide to the quarter marker then swung to the three path into upper stretch, vied for the lead at the furlong marker, dueled with MAJOR TOM into the final sixteenth, was carried out by his drifting stablemate in the final strides and was bested on the wire for the win, while clear of the rest for second. THECHIEFHASTRICKS rated nicely off of the decent early pace and saved ground into the turn, gained ground at the quarter marker and came in a bit tight nearing the top of the stretch, swung five wide into the lane and ran evenly to mid-stretch, could not impact the top pair in the final stages but closed well while widest in deep stretch and was up in time to secure third. R HEART OF GOLD was forwardly placed in the early running while outside of rivals, chased three wide into the turn and advanced at the quarter marker, was coaxed along four wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker and could not muster a late rally. MIGHTY RULER was hustled to establish the early lead, set decent fractions into the turn and extended the lead midway through the bend, showed the way into the stretch while off of the rail, was confronted by the top pair in upper stretch, met those bids to the furlong grounds and weakened. LUCKY RAPPER was slow into stride away from the gate and was outrun.

ALMOST SNOW showed speed in the early running and assumed command away from the gate, set a fast pace while pressured into the turn, carved out solid fractions while pressed by his stablemate to the quarter marker, battled with NO ICE NO GLASS to the furlong grounds, weakened into deep stretch and was clear in the end for third. I'M GONNA SHINE was forwardly placed while outside of rivals early on and stalked the pace three wide along the first turn, advanced along the backstretch run, came three wide into the far turn and vied for the lead nearing the quarter marker, battled for the lead into upper stretch and took command heading to the furlong grounds, was kept to task under steady urging into the final sixteenth, was confronted by OH ANGEL in deep stretch and was tagged for the win in the final strides, while besting the rest. CRESCENDO MOLTO settled leaving the start, came in a bit tight approaching the first turn, steadied off of heels and in turn carried out SILVER FLIRT leaving the seven furlong pole, regrouped and raced two wide into the backstretch run, improved position approaching the half-mile marker, was guided three wide into the far turn, swung four wide into the stretch, was not able to impact the top two in the final furlong but offered a mild late rally and was up in time to secure third. GLORIOUS DIVINITY broke alertly and assumed command in the early running, set moderate fractions while prompted into the backstretch run, showed the way while mildly pressured by VALERIE approaching the half-mile marker, lost the lead heading to the quarter pole, battled along the inside to mid-stretch, could not keep pace into the final sixteenth, gave way and was outfinished for third. VALERIE was a bit hard to handle and was keen in the early running, stalked the pace along the first turn, advanced to mildly pressure the moderate pace through the backstretch run, vied for the lead nearing the second turn and took a narrow advantage heading to the quarter marker, was overtaken in upper stretch, chased to the furlong grounds and tired in deep stretch. LIGHTS ASTERN settled just off of the early pace and saved ground into the first turn, improved position along the backstretch and was well placed heading to the far turn, was boxed in approaching the quarter marker, was outrun into the stretch and weakened in the final furlong. ENGLISH MEADOW was a bit hard to place in the early running, settled outside of rivals and tracked the moderate early pace, made a steady advance along the backstretch run, mounted a four wide bid at the quarter marker, could not sustain that run into the stretch and flattened out in the final stages. LIMITED HEATWAVE settled off of the early pace and raced outside of runners into the first turn, tracked the decent pace from the three path through the backstretch run, improved position while two wide at the quarter marker, slipped to the rail into upper stretch and loomed approaching the furlong pole, could not match strides with CARDIFF CRACK in the final sixteenth but finished well and was up in time to claim second. INCREDIBLE SHOT was forwardly placed leaving the start and tracked the early pace while three wide, was well positioned while outside of runners approaching the half-mile marker, advanced three wide along the far turn, swung to the four path into the stretch and ran evenly to the furlong marker, offered a mild late bid but lacked the needed response in deep stretch and was up in the final strides to secure third. OH GREAT (IRE) was asked for speed away from the gate and assumed command of the early running, showed the way into the first turn and set decent fractions through the backstretch while well handled, carved out the pace to the quarter marker and was set down into upper stretch, held foes at bay into the final furlong, was confronted by CARDIFF CRACK approaching the sixteenth-marker, met that bid into deep stretch but could not keep pace into the late stages, was outfinished and just missed for the minor awards.
